package concept

velocity: {
  content: #"""
    Velocity is the time derivative of the position vector, and velocity is
    rank-1 tensor:

    $ ub(v)(t) := ("d"ub(x))/("d"t) $

    Its components (given a basis ${ub(e)_j}$) are

    $ v_j = ub(v) ⋅ ub(e)_j = ("d"x_j)/("d"t) $

    Velocity is a *tangent vector* on the curve $cal("P")(λ)$, $ub(v)$ points
    along the direction of motion.
  """#
}